node.text:
“The first clip features a humpback whale rising from the middle of a baitball in absolutely perfect conditions! This whale's name is Snowflake. Snowflake is a very special whale to me as it is the first humpback whale I ever saw breach and the first whale that ever ‘mugged’ me…

“In the whale watching world, ‘mugging’ refers to the moment a whale sticks its head out of the water, making eye contact. Snowflake seemed to recognize our voices. It was a beautiful and life-changing moment.”

“The first clip features a humpback whale rising from the middle of a baitball in absolutely perfect conditions! This whale's name is Snowflake. Snowflake is a very special whale to me as it is the first humpback whale I ever saw breach and the first whale that ever ‘mugged’ me…

“In the whale watching world, ‘mugging’ refers to the moment a whale sticks its head out of the water, making eye contact. Snowflake seemed to recognize our voices. It was a beautiful and life-changing moment.”

node.text:
This made us stop and really ponder the power of these creatures.. 🦈
A great white shark, one of the largest sharks in the world, was seen emerging from the water and launching itself into the air. But this wasn’t an ordinary leap because it managed to get itself 15 feet (4.57 meters) above water. In context, a typical shark will jump up to 8-10 feet (2.4–3 meters) above water. For this reason, seeing a shark soar another 5 feet above this mark makes a record-breaking breach.
📹 @discovery
